00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:19.920
He never talked about his struggles

00:10:19.920 --> 00:10:23.140
when he was growing
up, but he had many.

00:10:23.140 --> 00:10:26.420
He came to this country
when he was three years old,

00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:30.450
settled in Mercedes, Texas, to
escape the Mexican Revolution.

00:10:30.450 --> 00:10:32.550
They had ten children.

00:10:32.550 --> 00:10:35.400
His father and mother
had ten children.

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:41.070 position:56%
Out of the seven surviving children,
six of them became medical doctors.

00:10:41.070 --> 00:10:49.140
Now, if you think about that in
the 1940s and 1950s, Dr. Hector,

00:10:49.140 --> 00:10:52.010
Dr. J.A. and Dr. Cleo all
went to the University

00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:55.120
of Texas Medical Branch
in Galveston.

00:10:55.120 --> 00:10:58.820
The other children went to
Medical School in Mexico.

00:10:58.820 --> 00:11:03.070
But there were six practicing
physicians in that one family.

00:11:03.070 --> 00:11:05.150
Now, you wonder how,
how did that happen?

00:11:05.150 --> 00:11:08.020
Well, he had a very strict father.

00:11:08.020 --> 00:11:10.450
He went to segregated
schools, so his parents,

00:11:10.450 --> 00:11:12.970
his father would take the
children into the basement

00:11:12.970 --> 00:11:17.710
and teach them things like history,
English, things that they needed

00:11:17.710 --> 00:11:21.240
to know because he wanted
his family to succeed.

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:23.500
So, that's how they got it done.

00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:26.460
I mean, this is what we have to
teach our children, you know,

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:29.910
