00:12:30.070 --> 00:12:32.810
So, he ended up in Omaha, Nebraska,

00:12:32.810 --> 00:12:35.790
St. Joseph's Hospital,
Creighton University.

00:12:35.790 --> 00:12:41.540
And I remember this story, telling
me that, oh, they sent some doctors

00:12:41.540 --> 00:12:46.260
down to Galveston, and we really
liked them, so we decided to go

00:12:46.260 --> 00:12:50.040
with them all the way to
Omaha in the freezing weather,

00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:55.530
and from South Texas this did not
go well for him, going into Omaha.

00:12:55.530 --> 00:12:59.950
But the truth was no one
would take him, no one.

00:12:59.950 --> 00:13:02.310 position:56%
So, he went there for his two years.

00:13:02.310 --> 00:13:08.130
He then got called to
active military duty.

00:13:08.130 --> 00:13:13.890 position:56%
