00:28:58.950 --> 00:29:02.990 position:56%
"Dr. Hector P. Garcia would
achieve a high rank in the military,

00:29:02.990 --> 00:29:05.820
but he would never forget
about the soldiers who fought

00:29:05.820 --> 00:29:07.570
with him in World War II.

00:29:07.570 --> 00:29:12.060 position:56%
He felt an obligation to all the
military members he would encounter,

00:29:12.060 --> 00:29:15.540
to the organization he
founded, the American GI Forum.

00:29:15.540 --> 00:29:18.880
This was clearly evident
during the Vietnam War.

00:29:18.880 --> 00:29:22.300
He was very saddened by all the
soldiers who were being returned

00:29:22.300 --> 00:29:26.510
to Corpus Christi to their families
after being killed in this war.

00:29:26.510 --> 00:29:30.140
He made efforts every day
to comfort the families.

00:29:30.140 --> 00:29:33.800
He would be notified when one of
these young men would be returning

00:29:33.800 --> 00:29:35.980
to his family in a coffin.

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:39.140
He would make arrangements with
other American GI Forum members

00:29:39.140 --> 00:29:41.150
to meet the returning soldiers

00:29:41.150 --> 00:29:44.780
at the Corpus Christi
[inaudible] station or the airport,

00:29:44.780 --> 00:29:47.170
regardless of the time of day.

00:29:47.170 --> 00:29:51.340 position:56%
If needed, my father would refer
the families to a local funeral home

00:29:51.340 --> 00:29:55.620
for interment and funeral
services at a very low cost.

00:29:55.620 --> 00:29:58.450
The funeral home was happy
to assist these families

00:29:58.450 --> 00:30:00.400
