"There's not one picture
of papa in this book."

00:46:19.750 --> 00:46:21.320
I said, "Well, let
me come over there."

00:46:21.320 --> 00:46:24.300
So, we went over there,
and she just lived

00:46:24.300 --> 00:46:25.810
about seven minutes from my house.

00:46:25.810 --> 00:46:28.940
She had a beautiful apartment
that we set her up in

00:46:28.940 --> 00:46:32.440
and was well taken care of
till the end of her life.

00:46:32.440 --> 00:46:38.590
But we went over there, and to
see your 84-year-old mother crying

00:46:38.590 --> 00:46:43.700
like that, and she wouldn't stop.

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:49.030
And that, I think that really
impacted me because she was saying,

00:46:49.030 --> 00:46:50.650
"No one knows who papa is.

00:46:50.650 --> 00:46:53.200
No one knows what he
did for this country.

00:46:53.200 --> 00:46:54.500
No one knows about him,

00:46:54.500 --> 00:46:57.010
and the American GI Forum
was not promoting him."

00:46:57.010 --> 00:47:01.000
So, that day, we made
a promise to her

00:47:01.000 --> 00:47:06.240
that we would do whatever we
needed to to have my father

00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:09.190
at the historical level
that he needed to be.

00:47:09.190 --> 00:47:12.700
And so that's how we got started,
that one phone call from her.

00:47:12.700 --> 00:47:20.940 position:56%
And to our credit, really, it really
needed to be done by the family

00:47:20.940 --> 00:47:24.660
because we knew it needed
to be done correctly.

00:47:24.660 --> 00:47:30.590
But you know, he really needs to
be at a different level than he is

00:47:30.590 --> 00:47:35.450
and recognized because of
everything that he did.

00:47:35.450 --> 00:47:41.630
And there's a bio in the back about
